observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Municipal Mayor, the members of the Municipal Planning and Development Council, Municipal Planning and Development Officer and all Municipal Officials concerned agreed to:

Ensure that development projects to be funded out of the 20% Development Fund are well-planned and procurement-and implementation-ready;

Implement the development projects programmed during the year as embodied in the AIP and ensure optimum utilization of the 20% Development Fund in compliance with the provisions of DILG and DBM JMC No. 2017-1;

Hasten the implementation of unutilized PPAs under continuing appropriation.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to:
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to summarize and submit a list of all unreleased checks to the Municipal Accountant at the end of the year;
Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries for all verified unreleased/ unclaimed checks in order to properly present the cash in bank account and recognize the corresponding liability accounts in the Financial Statements.

Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to coordinate and obtain the necessary documents to support valid reconciling items and make appropriate adjustments in the BRS to fairly present the balances of Cash in Bank Accounts in the Financial Statements;
Municipal Treasurer and the Municipal Accountant to verify and monitor all check releases and ensure the proper presentation and classification of outstanding checks in the Bank Reconciliation Statements; and
Municipal Accountant to retrieve the original copy of checks and its supporting documents for all verified stale checks in order to facilitate the preparation of adjusting entries to correct the balance of Cash in Bank.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant to:

1. Reclassify the fund transfer from Other MOOE to Due from other LGUs;

2. Monitor and require the liquidation reports from the recipient LGUs;




We also recommended that the MPDO submit copy of the agreed policy and procedures in the monitoring of PAPs and the corresponding report thereon.

We  recommended  that  the  Municipal  Mayor  instruct  the  Municipal Accountant to:

1. Reclassify the fund transfer from Other  MOOE  to  Due  from  other LGUs;
2. Monitor and require the  liquidation  reports  from  the  recipient LGUs;
3. Comply with the requirements provided in COA Circular  No.  2012-001 and other pertinent laws, rules and regulations.

We also recommended that the MPDO submit copy of the agreed policy and procedures in the monitoring of  PAPs  and  the  corresponding report thereon.

We recommended that the:

City Mayor stop the grant of cash advance for purposes other than those provided in COA Circular No. 97-002;

City Treasurer ensure that all payments to suppliers are made through checks in accordance with the imprest system of disbursements to give reasonable assurance that funds are fully safeguarded against loss, misuse or misappropriation;

Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) make sure that the threshold amount for shopping is complied with and only those that are emergency in nature be purchased thru shopping;

Special Disbursing Officers and other accountable/liable officers refund the amount of P243,300.00 representing excess meals purchased as against the number of attendees;


OIC-City Accountant to examine thoroughly the liquidation reports and their supporting documents before recording to avoid possible suspension and/or disallowances in audit; and

BAC to submit explanation as to the mode of procurement used and/or documentary requirements relative to the transaction, such as: a) BAC Resolution recommending to Head of the Procuring Entity (HOPE) the use of alternative mode of procurement and approval by the HOPE of the BAC Resolution recommending the award of the contract; b) Abstract of Canvass documents for shopping; and c) Certification as to the completeness of the project and/or Accomplishment Report.
